31 shall be entitled to retain as gross profit not more than 30 per cent of the resale value of tickets
32 sold by it, and shall be solely responsible for paying prizes won by tickets sold by it, which
33 prizes shall be determined by the commission and be not less than 45 per cent of the resale value
34 of said tickets.
35 The commission shall sell lottery tickets to said licensed organizations for 10 per cent of
36 their resale value; provided further, 10 per cent of the resale value of digital pull tab tickets shall
37 revert to the commission, . The revenue derived by the commission from said sales of lottery
38 tickets or digital pull tab tickets shall be apportioned as follows: (1) for the payment of costs;
39 provided, however, that notwithstanding the provisions of section 25, the costs incurred by the
40 commission in the operation and administration of the activities authorized by this section,
41 including the expenses of the commission and the costs resulting from any contract or contracts
42 entered into for promotional, advertising or operational service or for the purchase or lease of
43 lottery equipment, materials and tickets, in no case shall exceed one half of said revenue, subject
44 to appropriation; (2) the balance of said revenue, as determined by the comptroller on June 1 and
45 December 1 of each year, shall be credited to the State Lottery and Gaming Fund to be
46 distributed in accordance with the provisions of section 18C of chapter 58.
47 Organizations licensed under this section shall be considered sales agents for the
48 purposes of this chapter. Activities authorized by this section shall be subject to all provisions of
49 the state lottery law not inconsistent herewith.
